.9 MB","code":"/**\\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\\n * public class TreeNode {\\n *     int val;\\n *     TreeNode left;\\n *     TreeNode right;\\n *     TreeNode() {}\\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\\n *         this.val = val;\\n *         this.left = left;\\n *         this.right = right;\\n *     }\\n * }\\n */\\nclass Solution {\\n    public int kthSmallest(TreeNode root, int k) {\\n        Deque<TreeNode> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();\\n        TreeNode current = root;\\n\\n        while((current != null)||(!stack.isEmpty())){\\n            while(current != null){\\n                stack.push(current);\\n                current = current.left;\\n            }\\n\\n            current = stack.pop();\\n            k--;\\n            if(k==0)return current.val;\\n            current = current.right;\\n        }\\n        return -1;\\n    }\\n}","compare_result":"111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111","title_slug":"kth-smallest-element-in-a-bst","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1,"frontend_id":562},{"id":1922962891,"question_id":230,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"4\xc2\xa0months, 2\xc2\xa0weeks","timestamp":1771397038,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"0 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1922962891/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Kth Smallest Element in a BST","memory":"47.1 MB","code":"/**\\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\\n * public class TreeNode {\\n *     int val;\\n *     TreeNode left;\\n *     TreeNode right;\\n *     TreeNode() {}\\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\\n *         this.val = val;\\n *         this.left = left;\\n *         this.right = right;\\n *     }\\n * }\\n */\\nclass Solution {\\n    public int kthSmallest(TreeNode root, int k) {\\n        Deque<TreeNode> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();\\n        Tr